cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MA, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with interference management in wireless networks. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper uses autoregressive moving average (ARMA) models to predict interference values. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper proposes a recursive filtering technique to predict interference. 
4. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is a possible category as the paper discusses the applicability of the predictor in underlay device-to-device communications. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) is a less likely category as the paper does not explicitly deal with multimedia, but it does discuss the applicability of the predictor in wireless sensor technology.
